1
00:00:04,880 --> 00:00:06,600
Twenty-two minutes.

2
00:00:06,640 --> 00:00:09,680
That's how long your
computer's been inactive.

3
00:00:09,720 --> 00:00:11,440
What were you doing in there?

4
00:00:11,480 --> 00:00:12,520
Faffing around?

5
00:00:12,560 --> 00:00:15,400
Watching the latest episode of
So You Think You Can Dillydally?

6
00:00:15,440 --> 00:00:18,000
You can't ask me that.

7
00:00:18,040 --> 00:00:19,960
So not a denial per se.

8
00:00:20,520 --> 00:00:23,840
I shall be alerting
the wage-garnishers.

9
00:00:27,920 --> 00:00:29,880
Bit quicker.

10
00:00:29,920 --> 00:00:32,640
They are only allowed
to work on the newspaper

11
00:00:32,680 --> 00:00:34,120
couple of hours a day.

12
00:00:34,160 --> 00:00:38,920
Now, this program here, voila,
that lets me know whenever

13
00:00:38,960 --> 00:00:40,600
their computer is inactive.

14
00:00:40,640 --> 00:00:42,640
And! Here we go!

15
00:00:42,680 --> 00:00:46,840
Oscar hasn't touched his
spreadsheet for 15 minutes.

16
00:00:46,880 --> 00:00:48,080
Oh, dear.

17
00:00:48,120 --> 00:00:50,600
You're scamming the company, mate.

18
00:00:50,640 --> 00:00:53,640
I'm so tired of asking
Adam to move my mouse

19
00:00:53,680 --> 00:00:54,760
every time I'm out on a story.

20
00:00:54,800 --> 00:00:56,440
I've got my own mouse
to worry about.

21
00:00:56,480 --> 00:00:57,960
You guys wanna see something crazy?

22
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:00,560
- Uh-oh.
- I call it The Mouse Nudger.

23
00:01:00,600 --> 00:01:02,320
Watch this.

24
00:01:06,520 --> 00:01:07,960
- Whoa.
- Oh, man.

25
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:09,560
Oh, my God, look!

26
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:12,039
Mm-hmm. So no matter
where Mare goes,

27
00:01:12,080 --> 00:01:14,120
her mouse keeps moving,
keeping her computer awake.

28
00:01:14,160 --> 00:01:17,160
Mare could literally
vanish and it wouldn't matter.

29
00:01:17,240 --> 00:01:19,680
Well, it'd matter. To some.

30
00:01:19,720 --> 00:01:20,840
How did you make that so fast?

31
00:01:20,920 --> 00:01:23,080
It's something I designed
to stuff down the throat

32
00:01:23,120 --> 00:01:25,720
of a dead frog to make it wiggle,
so a trout would wanna eat it.

33
00:01:25,760 --> 00:01:28,840
And I was confident enough
to make about 144 of them.

34
00:01:28,880 --> 00:01:31,560
But the suits at Bass
Pro Shops didn't get it.

35
00:01:31,680 --> 00:01:33,120
Shall I put you all down for one?

36
00:01:33,160 --> 00:01:34,200
Oh.

37
00:01:34,240 --> 00:01:37,840
"Ken Davies has just
invited you to get back to work."

38
00:01:37,880 --> 00:01:39,520
- Jesus.
- You know what, I'll take one.

39
00:01:39,560 --> 00:01:42,800
- Yeah. Can I take two?
- Yeah, me too.

40
00:01:42,840 --> 00:01:44,640
Everyone busy, busy.

41
00:01:44,680 --> 00:01:46,080
My little dwarves.

42
00:01:46,120 --> 00:01:49,800
And I'm Snow White, their boss.

43
00:01:49,840 --> 00:01:53,479
The tough but fairest of them all.

44
00:01:59,240 --> 00:02:01,520
You gotta put it in six times.

45
00:02:01,560 --> 00:02:05,480
One, two, three, four, five... Oh!

46
00:02:05,520 --> 00:02:07,840
- Here, you woke Daddy!
- Sorry to freak you out!

47
00:02:07,880 --> 00:02:09,280
You all woke Daddy!

48
00:02:37,360 --> 00:02:40,760
Marv and some of his team
are working on this floor

49
00:02:40,800 --> 00:02:42,240
while his offices are being painted.

50
00:02:42,360 --> 00:02:44,920
Which means he can see
everything that we're doing.

51
00:02:44,960 --> 00:02:46,360
We're enjoying this meeting.

52
00:02:46,400 --> 00:02:47,880
Everyone's sort of nodding.

53
00:02:47,920 --> 00:02:48,960
- Nodding a little bit.
- Ok.

54
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:50,040
- Yes.
- Right.

55
00:02:50,079 --> 00:02:51,760
Yes, I am actively agreeing
with you.

56
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:54,240
Now you act like you came
up with another good idea...

57
00:02:54,280 --> 00:02:55,360
Put up your hand. Yes!

58
00:02:55,400 --> 00:02:57,200
- I don't know what you want...
- Yes! Yes, yes!

59
00:02:57,240 --> 00:02:59,520
That is a great idea.
I'm gonna write that down.

60
00:02:59,560 --> 00:03:01,080
Does that look like
I'm writing it down?

61
00:03:01,120 --> 00:03:02,640
- Yeah. Yeah. Yeah?
- Good. Good, good.

62
00:03:02,680 --> 00:03:05,280
This is weird. Maybe we
should just have a real meeting...

63
00:03:05,400 --> 00:03:06,880
Now, Adelola, you're pointing.

64
00:03:06,920 --> 00:03:09,640
You're pointing and everyone's
nodding and I am agreeing.

65
00:03:09,680 --> 00:03:11,360
And Barry, you stand up,
you stand up.

66
00:03:11,400 --> 00:03:14,360
I think everyone's nodding now.
We're all nodding at Barry. Yes.

67
00:03:14,400 --> 00:03:16,560
Now Detrick, you're gonna
jump out with enthusiasm.

68
00:03:16,600 --> 00:03:18,840
You're gonna high five Oscar!

69
00:03:18,880 --> 00:03:20,320
Go! Yes, and, oh!

70
00:03:20,360 --> 00:03:24,200
Fantastic. Fantastic, and we're
clapping, we're clapping

71
00:03:24,240 --> 00:03:25,400
and we're thumbs-upping.

72
00:03:25,440 --> 00:03:27,000
We're thumbs-upping
and we're nodding.

73
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:29,120
Feel the energy. and we're smiling.

74
00:03:32,440 --> 00:03:35,240
That was the most fun
meeting we've ever had!

75
00:03:35,280 --> 00:03:37,000
- Yeah?
- Ok, fantastic.

76
00:03:37,040 --> 00:03:38,760
- Thank you so much.
- Impressive.

77
00:03:38,840 --> 00:03:40,720
Stop, stop. Too much, too much.

78
00:03:40,760 --> 00:03:41,960
Welcome, sir!

79
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:43,360
Didn't know you were here.

80
00:03:43,400 --> 00:03:45,079
I hope the fumes
aren't too bad down there.

81
00:03:45,120 --> 00:03:46,760
I know this is distracting.

82
00:03:46,800 --> 00:03:48,760
But we won't get in your way.

83
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:51,480
Oh, no. Not at all.
It is fantastic to have you here.

84
00:03:51,520 --> 00:03:53,720
And I don't know.
Do you need anything or...?

85
00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:55,440
I think I know my way around.

86
00:03:56,720 --> 00:03:58,280
Oh, very good.

87
00:03:58,320 --> 00:04:00,480
Well, our floor is your floor.

88
00:04:00,520 --> 00:04:02,920
Usually your floor is my ceiling.

89
00:04:04,760 --> 00:04:06,160
Boom, fantastic.

90
00:04:06,200 --> 00:04:10,080
Some people tend to lose all dignity
in the face of their betters.

91
00:04:10,120 --> 00:04:14,000
Fortunately, it usually
gets them precisely nowhere.

92
00:04:14,040 --> 00:04:17,680
Men of quality... Your
Marv Putnams of this world.

93
00:04:17,720 --> 00:04:19,640
...they can see right through you.

94
00:04:19,680 --> 00:04:25,400
Yeah... That is excellent, My Liege!

95
00:04:25,440 --> 00:04:28,280
- Alright. Back to work!
- Sounds good.

96
00:04:28,320 --> 00:04:30,160
- Happy to have you.
- Be off with you.

97
00:04:59,880 --> 00:05:03,000
I don't have to be friends
with everybody I work with.

98
00:05:03,040 --> 00:05:06,240
I mean, I'm not friends with Ken.

99
00:05:06,280 --> 00:05:08,320
And Ken's, you know, never...

100
00:05:08,360 --> 00:05:10,280
assumed something about me so
incorrectly

101
00:05:10,320 --> 00:05:12,240
I spend all weekend going
through my makeup and clothes

102
00:05:12,280 --> 00:05:14,000
and facial expressions in the mirror,
trying to...

103
00:05:14,040 --> 00:05:16,920
I'm sorry, do you guys ever
ask questions about journalism?

104
00:05:17,040 --> 00:05:18,200
Hey, Marv.

105
00:05:18,240 --> 00:05:20,120
November 1984.

106
00:05:20,160 --> 00:05:22,800
A profile of a certain
up-and-coming local businessman

107
00:05:22,840 --> 00:05:25,120
that you might recognize.

108
00:05:25,160 --> 00:05:26,200
Whoa.

109
00:05:26,240 --> 00:05:28,000
Look at that kid.

110
00:05:28,080 --> 00:05:29,520
What happened to all my hair?

111
00:05:29,560 --> 00:05:31,080
Huh. I don't know.

112
00:05:31,160 --> 00:05:33,600
And also, we got your obituary.

113
00:05:33,640 --> 00:05:35,400
- What?
- As a prominent Toledon,

114
00:05:35,440 --> 00:05:37,680
we will have it ready to go for you
the second you die.

115
00:05:37,800 --> 00:05:39,400
Maybe even a little bit before.

116
00:05:39,440 --> 00:05:41,440
"Marvin Putnam, the end."

117
00:05:41,480 --> 00:05:42,760
- Hey!
- Hey.

118
00:05:42,800 --> 00:05:44,600
I was just showing Marv
some times that he was

119
00:05:44,640 --> 00:05:47,480
or will be in the paper. Like,
"Marvin Putnam, the end."

120
00:05:47,520 --> 00:05:49,000
Stop saying that.

121
00:05:49,040 --> 00:05:51,600
"A graduate of DePauw,
Putnam lettered in tennis before

122
00:05:51,640 --> 00:05:54,200
joining Hamilton Mills in 1982.

123
00:05:54,240 --> 00:05:58,720
For the next 40 blank years,
he oversaw the financial..."

124
00:05:59,960 --> 00:06:01,360
Wow.

125
00:06:01,400 --> 00:06:03,880
Not exactly Warren Buffet.

126
00:06:03,920 --> 00:06:07,480
Hey, Marv, have you met Detrick?

127
00:06:07,520 --> 00:06:09,520
Hey, Detrick, this is Marv,
he's in sales too.

128
00:06:09,560 --> 00:06:11,800
- Hey, how are you?
- How'd your weekend go, kid?

129
00:06:12,880 --> 00:06:15,040
I caught the second half.
Go Mudhens?

130
00:06:15,080 --> 00:06:17,320
It's always hard when
the head honcho is around.

131
00:06:17,360 --> 00:06:18,680
For some reason
when he's talking to me,

132
00:06:18,720 --> 00:06:21,840
I start thinking about
the way my dad looked

133
00:06:21,880 --> 00:06:23,040
during my little league games.

134
00:06:23,080 --> 00:06:26,240
It's... It's like he'd have
an empty look in his eyes.

135
00:06:26,280 --> 00:06:29,160
And I'd just be at bat, wondering,
like, where his mind had

136
00:06:29,200 --> 00:06:30,440
taken him in those moments.

137
00:06:31,360 --> 00:06:33,159
And then I realize
Marv is still talking,

138
00:06:33,200 --> 00:06:35,440
and I have no idea
what the hell he's saying.

139
00:06:35,480 --> 00:06:37,880
Right, they were down
three in the top of the eighth.

140
00:06:39,280 --> 00:06:40,960
I skateboard to work.

141
00:06:45,240 --> 00:06:47,360
- Hey, uh...
- Oh, it's Travis, sir.

142
00:06:47,400 --> 00:06:49,720
- Right. How's your day going?
- Everything is fine,

143
00:06:49,760 --> 00:06:51,680
and I love working here,
thank you.

144
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:55,159
I can't stand it when
people lose their spine

145
00:06:55,200 --> 00:06:58,000
the second a person higher up
on the pay scale notices them.

146
00:06:58,040 --> 00:07:00,280
It's like the hidden
cost of capitalism.

147
00:07:00,320 --> 00:07:03,120
Like, your labor is not enough,
they want your dignity too.

148
00:07:03,160 --> 00:07:04,520
I do not play that game.

149
00:07:05,960 --> 00:07:07,520
- Hi.
- Hey.

150
00:07:10,360 --> 00:07:11,680
- Hello.
- Hey.

151
00:07:11,760 --> 00:07:14,360
Marv said these are all approved.

152
00:07:15,400 --> 00:07:18,480
These are the stories
I said we're not doing.

153
00:07:18,520 --> 00:07:22,000
I know.
But Marv thought differently.

154
00:07:22,040 --> 00:07:23,240
He says they have spice.

155
00:07:23,280 --> 00:07:25,840
You, uh...
You can't go over my head.

156
00:07:25,880 --> 00:07:28,440
Are you calling me short?

157
00:07:28,480 --> 00:07:30,800
I go directly to HR.

158
00:07:36,480 --> 00:07:38,360
Do you have an appointment?

159
00:07:38,400 --> 00:07:40,840
I just wanna ask a question.

160
00:07:41,720 --> 00:07:43,680
I didn't see you in Marv's schedule,
mate.

161
00:07:43,720 --> 00:07:46,280
Listen. Just because the boss
is on your floor,

162
00:07:46,320 --> 00:07:48,600
it doesn't mean that
you've gone up in the world.

163
00:07:48,640 --> 00:07:52,360
You're like a child
sitting on a pilot's lap

164
00:07:52,400 --> 00:07:54,159
who thinks he's flying the plane.

165
00:07:54,200 --> 00:07:56,080
Well, guess what? He's not.

166
00:07:56,120 --> 00:07:58,120
They're not insured for that.

167
00:07:58,960 --> 00:08:00,880
- Careful.
- Hey.

168
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:02,360
Hey, buddy. How you doing?

169
00:08:02,440 --> 00:08:04,800
You know Kimberly
here just sold her one

170
00:08:04,840 --> 00:08:07,320
millionth roll of Softees?

171
00:08:07,880 --> 00:08:09,880
- Can we chat?
- Sure.

172
00:08:09,920 --> 00:08:11,920
Yeah? Thanks.

173
00:08:11,960 --> 00:08:13,840
Don't.

174
00:08:19,720 --> 00:08:22,040
The golden boy.

175
00:08:22,080 --> 00:08:24,000
He's coming for me.

176
00:08:24,040 --> 00:08:26,640
I can tell, he's coming for me.

177
00:08:27,160 --> 00:08:28,240
Imagine that.

178
00:08:28,280 --> 00:08:31,160
Losing your job to Ned
bloody Sampson, how pathetic.

179
00:08:32,280 --> 00:08:33,280
Sorry.

180
00:08:34,039 --> 00:08:36,159
Why is Ned so good with Marv?

181
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:38,360
- Why do you think?
- Hm.

182
00:08:38,400 --> 00:08:39,960
- I don't know.
- One percent.

183
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:41,919
They have a shorthand.

184
00:08:41,960 --> 00:08:43,640
A secret language.

185
00:08:43,679 --> 00:08:44,880
Like Bulgarian.

186
00:08:44,920 --> 00:08:48,280
If I ever say anything to
Marv that I wouldn't say to you,

187
00:08:48,320 --> 00:08:50,000
I want you to slap me.

188
00:08:50,040 --> 00:08:51,480
- Put it in writing.
- Sure.

189
00:08:51,520 --> 00:08:53,880
It's so great that you're here.

190
00:08:53,920 --> 00:08:56,200
It's a real shot in the arm.

191
00:08:56,240 --> 00:08:58,400
- Thanks, kid.
- If I can be honest,

192
00:08:58,440 --> 00:09:03,680
I think it's very exciting
that you're here to the team.

193
00:09:03,720 --> 00:09:05,200
And it might actually be

194
00:09:05,240 --> 00:09:08,160
a little more than they can handle.

195
00:09:08,200 --> 00:09:09,360
I overstepped.

196
00:09:09,400 --> 00:09:12,080
- Oh, no. Not at all.
- No Grandpa giving out sweets.

197
00:09:12,120 --> 00:09:14,400
- No! No, not that at all.
- Big boss daddy with the fancy tie.

198
00:09:14,440 --> 00:09:15,720
It is fantastic that you're here.

199
00:09:15,760 --> 00:09:17,960
- It's fantastic. I just...
- I got it.

200
00:09:19,240 --> 00:09:20,440
I got it.

201
00:09:21,440 --> 00:09:23,160
Thanks, Marv.

202
00:09:23,200 --> 00:09:25,560
Old Ned playing the game.

203
00:09:26,080 --> 00:09:28,000
Didn't know he had it in him.

204
00:09:28,040 --> 00:09:30,280
They're bonding. I think it's sweet.

205
00:09:30,320 --> 00:09:31,800
No, no, no.

206
00:09:31,840 --> 00:09:35,400
Groveling, sniveling, conniving.

207
00:09:35,440 --> 00:09:36,840
Scheming.

208
00:09:36,880 --> 00:09:38,160
The Ginger Machiavelli.

209
00:09:38,240 --> 00:09:39,560
Whoa!

210
00:09:39,600 --> 00:09:42,840
Looks like they're
almost done fixing our floor.

211
00:09:42,880 --> 00:09:46,360
Be good, kiddo. Love you.

212
00:09:48,320 --> 00:09:50,240
Men of that age, my father's age

213
00:09:50,280 --> 00:09:52,560
don't often get to hear I love you.

214
00:09:52,600 --> 00:09:55,120
Mostly because they don't say it.

215
00:09:56,480 --> 00:09:58,640
But he said it.

216
00:09:58,680 --> 00:10:01,080
He absolutely said it.

217
00:10:01,680 --> 00:10:03,080
Marv!

218
00:10:04,040 --> 00:10:05,480
I love you.

219
00:10:09,840 --> 00:10:11,760
Yeah. Love you, bud.

220
00:10:11,800 --> 00:10:13,400
Love this.

221
00:10:14,360 --> 00:10:15,480
We need to talk.

222
00:10:15,520 --> 00:10:17,520
Take the service elevator down to B.

223
00:10:22,120 --> 00:10:23,480
- Hey, Oscar?
- Mm-hmm?

224
00:10:23,520 --> 00:10:26,960
I need those purchase orders
and, um...

225
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:28,520
I love you.

226
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:31,000
- Sent.
- Thank you.

227
00:10:31,040 --> 00:10:34,560
And I love you more
than the moon and stars.

228
00:10:34,600 --> 00:10:36,880
Hey,
there's no shame in publicly showing

229
00:10:36,920 --> 00:10:38,600
love to another man in the workplace,
Ok?

230
00:10:38,640 --> 00:10:40,840
Me and Garcia say we
love each other all the time.

231
00:10:40,880 --> 00:10:42,640
Watch this. Love you, Garcia!

232
00:10:42,680 --> 00:10:44,040
Love you, man!

233
00:10:44,080 --> 00:10:45,960
Hey, Detrick.

234
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:48,200
- Love you, bro.
- What?

235
00:10:48,240 --> 00:10:50,840
I'm just a boy,
standing in front of his boss...

236
00:10:50,960 --> 00:10:53,120
That's not something to joke about.

237
00:10:53,160 --> 00:10:55,160
- Love, Actually?
- Hm, Yeah.

238
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:57,080
It's Notting Hill, but whatever.

239
00:10:58,720 --> 00:11:00,880
- Hey, Casanova?
- Huh?

240
00:11:00,920 --> 00:11:02,760
You coming for my ass next?

241
00:11:03,400 --> 00:11:06,000
Oh, I was, uh,
hoping nobody noticed that.

242
00:11:06,040 --> 00:11:08,600
I noticed.
That's why I made that remark.

243
00:11:08,640 --> 00:11:10,680
Yeah, I would say people clocked it

244
00:11:10,720 --> 00:11:11,880
when you declared your feelings

245
00:11:11,920 --> 00:11:13,320
for the guy who runs the company.

246
00:11:13,360 --> 00:11:14,960
You think they'll
make a thing out of it?

247
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:16,000
Hey, Ned.

248
00:11:16,040 --> 00:11:19,360
I just wanna let you know,
um, you complete me.

249
00:11:19,400 --> 00:11:21,440
I think they'll
make a thing out of it.

250
00:11:21,480 --> 00:11:23,720
Just curious, do your dad and Marv

251
00:11:23,760 --> 00:11:24,800
go to the same yacht club?

252
00:11:24,840 --> 00:11:26,120
Ha! Ok. Ha, ha!

253
00:11:26,160 --> 00:11:29,120
My dad doesn't have a yacht. Ok?

254
00:11:29,160 --> 00:11:31,840
He's a pilot.
He owns a Piper Cub twin engine.

255
00:11:31,880 --> 00:11:36,880
He once had to crash land in a field,
like Harrison Ford.

