I heard what you did.

508
00:21:48,880 --> 00:21:51,120
That man keeps the lights
on over your head,

509
00:21:51,160 --> 00:21:52,440
and this is how you thank him?

510
00:21:52,480 --> 00:21:53,800
By ordering him out
of his own newsroom?

511
00:21:53,840 --> 00:21:55,280
And by letting that dimwit

512
00:21:55,320 --> 00:21:58,320
show him a two-paragraph obituary
that doesn't do him justice!

513
00:21:58,360 --> 00:22:00,880
What's wrong with you today, Ned?

514
00:22:00,960 --> 00:22:03,080
Make it right!

515
00:22:05,080 --> 00:22:06,760
God!

516
00:22:08,520 --> 00:22:09,880
Ned, she's not wrong.

517
00:22:09,920 --> 00:22:12,720
Marv can shut down
the Truth Teller if he feels like it.

518
00:22:12,760 --> 00:22:14,800
I think he's probably just
upset about the obituary,

519
00:22:14,840 --> 00:22:19,240
so we'll make it better
by writing him a better one.

520
00:22:19,280 --> 00:22:22,040
It'll be a nice gesture, right?
An obituary so amazing,

521
00:22:22,080 --> 00:22:23,800
he'll wish that people
were reading it

522
00:22:23,840 --> 00:22:25,760
in tomorrow's newspaper.

523
00:22:25,800 --> 00:22:28,480
Uh, I... That... It sounds like
a threat. It's not a threat.

524
00:22:28,520 --> 00:22:31,120
What's going on?
You seem so serious.

525
00:22:31,160 --> 00:22:33,480
Oh, we are serious,
I'm afraid, Marv.

526
00:22:33,520 --> 00:22:34,520
Ahem.

527
00:22:34,560 --> 00:22:36,680
We hate to be the ones
to break it to you.

528
00:22:36,720 --> 00:22:39,080
Yes. We hate this.

529
00:22:39,640 --> 00:22:44,240
- Um... -Go on.
- Nate Wells is taking drugs.

530
00:22:45,040 --> 00:22:47,720
- Nate Wells?
- Janitor.

531
00:22:47,760 --> 00:22:51,120
- Oh, Nate, yeah.
- Yeah.

532
00:22:51,160 --> 00:22:52,160
- Wow.
- Wow.

533
00:22:52,200 --> 00:22:54,000
- That's surprising.
- Yes.

534
00:22:54,040 --> 00:22:55,360
What kind of drugs?

535
00:22:55,400 --> 00:22:57,480
Well, synthetic mushrooms... Poppers,
whip-its,

536
00:22:57,520 --> 00:22:59,280
uppers, downers...
That make you hallucinate

537
00:22:59,320 --> 00:23:00,600
- and hear things.
- ...designer stuff.

538
00:23:00,640 --> 00:23:02,080
The man is delusional, Marv.

539
00:23:02,120 --> 00:23:03,200
He makes up stuff.

540
00:23:03,240 --> 00:23:04,800
Like, crazy stuff.

541
00:23:04,840 --> 00:23:06,960
Like, conspiracy stuff.

542
00:23:07,000 --> 00:23:08,520
Overthrows, backstabbing.

543
00:23:08,560 --> 00:23:11,760
One minute it'll be governments,
the next minute companies.

544
00:23:11,800 --> 00:23:12,840
Once a school.

545
00:23:12,880 --> 00:23:14,040
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

546
00:23:14,080 --> 00:23:15,960
It's fascinating
what imagination does

547
00:23:16,000 --> 00:23:20,320
when drugs come
bing-banging through.

548
00:23:20,360 --> 00:23:22,520
Gee whiz. Nate.

549
00:23:25,200 --> 00:23:28,720
- Yes, poor Nate.
- Poor old Nate.

550
00:23:29,160 --> 00:23:31,800
"He was a renaissance man,
"toilet paper, envelopes,

551
00:23:31,840 --> 00:23:33,480
paper towels, he did it all." Yeah.

552
00:23:33,520 --> 00:23:36,720
"It was only his flat feet
that kept him out of Vietnam,

553
00:23:36,760 --> 00:23:38,640
"but he finally managed to get there

554
00:23:38,680 --> 00:23:40,400
on a cruise four years ago."

555
00:23:40,440 --> 00:23:42,200
That's good, right? Nice.

556
00:23:42,240 --> 00:23:44,520
So he has no kids.
Should we put that?

557
00:23:44,560 --> 00:23:47,280
Like, "He is survived by no kids."

558
00:23:47,320 --> 00:23:48,560
He has no kids?

559
00:23:48,600 --> 00:23:50,120
- Is something wrong with him?
- No.

560
00:23:50,160 --> 00:23:51,560
I think we just don't mention that.

561
00:23:51,600 --> 00:23:53,720
His company is his children.

562
00:23:53,760 --> 00:23:54,840
That is beautiful.

563
00:23:54,880 --> 00:23:55,920
Wanna put it down?

564
00:23:55,960 --> 00:23:57,200
Yeah, put that down.

565
00:23:57,240 --> 00:23:58,400
He is survived by his company.

566
00:23:58,440 --> 00:24:01,280
No. His company is his children.

567
00:24:05,080 --> 00:24:07,160
- God in heaven.
- Mm.

568
00:24:07,200 --> 00:24:09,560
Please help my brother, Nate...

569
00:24:10,400 --> 00:24:15,480
...through this dark time
and lead him into the light.

570
00:24:15,520 --> 00:24:18,440
# Swing low #

571
00:24:18,480 --> 00:24:22,000
# Sweet chariot #

572
00:24:22,040 --> 00:24:27,560
# Coming for to carry me home #

573
00:24:28,160 --> 00:24:29,880
Hey. Do you have a minute?

574
00:24:30,400 --> 00:24:32,800
I've been working with
the staff this afternoon.

575
00:24:32,840 --> 00:24:37,080
We, uh, put something
together that I hope you enjoy.

576
00:24:38,160 --> 00:24:41,480
"Marv Putnam is dead.

577
00:24:41,520 --> 00:24:43,200
"He died yesterday.

578
00:24:43,240 --> 00:24:46,840
"He was not surrounded
by people who loved him.

579
00:24:46,880 --> 00:24:49,120
"He was surrounded...

580
00:24:49,160 --> 00:24:52,440
by people who adored him."

581
00:24:52,480 --> 00:24:54,000
Ned, what is this?

582
00:24:54,040 --> 00:24:55,920
Please. If you'll allow me,
we're about to get to a part

583
00:24:55,960 --> 00:24:57,560
I really think is
going to blow you away.

584
00:24:57,600 --> 00:24:59,640
We were tearing up just writing it.

585
00:24:59,680 --> 00:25:01,680
Ned,

586
00:25:01,720 --> 00:25:03,360
there's something going on, and...

587
00:25:03,400 --> 00:25:06,720
I can't say that
I'm not feeling it too.

588
00:25:06,760 --> 00:25:10,680
But it would mean the world to me,
if we don't actually discuss it.

589
00:25:11,720 --> 00:25:13,680
I'm not your daddy.

590
00:25:13,720 --> 00:25:16,720
This is a business. And we
don't shut down a newspaper

591
00:25:16,760 --> 00:25:20,520
because you wrote a bad
obituary or you acted weird.

592
00:25:20,560 --> 00:25:24,800
We'd shut it down because
you don't make any money.

593
00:25:24,840 --> 00:25:26,240
Yeah.

594
00:25:26,280 --> 00:25:31,000
I found out today that a very
sweet man has a drug problem.

595
00:25:31,040 --> 00:25:32,400
That's real.

596
00:25:33,040 --> 00:25:35,280
That's where
I'm gonna put my energy.

597
00:25:43,280 --> 00:25:47,960
True love isn't something
you just say out loud.

598
00:25:48,000 --> 00:25:51,000
Kids don't get that because
it's based on experience.

599
00:25:51,040 --> 00:25:52,320
Long experience.

600
00:25:52,440 --> 00:25:54,440
You don't have to say I love

601
00:25:54,480 --> 00:25:57,040
you to people you actually love.

602
00:25:57,080 --> 00:25:58,560
They know.

603
00:25:59,200 --> 00:26:00,560
Hey, Marv?

604
00:26:00,600 --> 00:26:02,800
Don't forget those Vitamin D pills.

605
00:26:02,840 --> 00:26:05,760
We need you. We need you healthy.

606
00:26:05,800 --> 00:26:07,720
See you tomorrow, Ann.

607
00:26:08,760 --> 00:26:10,240
Forty-two years.

608
00:26:10,840 --> 00:26:12,360
Couldn't do it without her.

609
00:26:13,520 --> 00:26:15,160
My brother's wife.

